  "description": [
    "Press Gets Sneak Preview As ASub Nears Completion By Pfc Joe Taylor AUH AFPS Staff Writer GROTON CONN ARIS The worlds first atomicpowered submarine the USS Nautilus wan unveiled here recently for what the Navy described as its first and last press tour as construc tion of the new underseas craft neirs completion The Nautilus is scheduled for launching 21 Jan and will be sponsored by Mrs 1 iwight D Eisenhower During the tour the visitors were allowed to examine every section of the submarine except the nuclear reactor compartment and the torpedo tubes Them two sections were covered with canvas and under constant armed guard The craft is being built by the Electric Boat Division of the Gen eral Dynamics Corp Although precise details of the sise speed range diving depth and fighting characteristics were not divulged because of security reasons It was revealed that the submarine is somewhat larger than any now in operation by the Navy It will be manned by be tween 75 and HO officers and men In appearance the Nautilus is similar to current fleettype subs except that Its prow has a blunt shape Instead of the usual knife like edge This Increases its"
